To install (tested only on Ubuntu 10.04):

1. Install and create virtualenv:

    $ apt-get install virtualenv
    $ virtualenv env

3. Enable virtualenv. Run all commands in this environment:

4. Install requirements:

    (videocurate)$ pip install -r requirements.txt

5. Copy local settings file:

    (videocurate)$ cd ninetyninepercentmedia
    (videocurate)$ cp settings_private_template.py settings_private.py

6.  Edit private_settings.py to add your desired values.  Defaults should work at first.

7.  (videocurate)$ python manage.py syncdb

5. Run development server:

    (videocurate)$ python manage.py runserver

That's it!  You can now access the site at http://127.0.0.1:8000
